<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-659-757  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 659 757.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Dec 4 1990 v4 n41 p32(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Augment card helps Mac II users move larger files faster. (AugmentSystems Inc.'s AL 101 NuBus and AL 102 VME communications board)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wylie, Margie.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Augment Systems Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh II (Microcomputer) (Equipment and supplies)Augment Systems AL 101 (Communications board) (Productintroduction)Augment Systems AL 102 (Communications board) (Productintroduction)Sun Microsystems SPARCstation (Workstation) (Equipment andsupplies).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCommunications Boards-Cards.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Margie WylieandM;Bedford, Mass.andP;  -- A new direct-link fiber-optic technology recentlyintroduced by Augment Systems Inc. promises Mac II users a way to move largefiles point-to-point at two to three times the throughput of FiberDistributed Data Interface networks.andM;Designed to complement, not replace LANs, the $3,699 AL 101 NuBus cardprovides direct bus-to-bus transfers at distances up to 2 kilometers, withoutthe overhead of network protocols.andP;  &quot;We just create a raw data bridge fromone bus to another,&quot; said Augment President Chap Cory.andP;  &quot;We don't provide forfile or protocol translation; we just move the data from one machine toanother, fast.&quot;andM;A manufacturer of composite aircraft wings uses the link to send imagesbetween a Mac in an office and another mounted on the factory ceiling thatcontrols a laser drawing wing patterns on the factory floor, according toCory.andM;&quot;Some people might use the link in a scientific or engineering context tomove big blocks of data around, but we see its primary use in shippingimages, such as X-rays or CAT scans in a hospital setting,&quot; he said.andM;The card also comes in a VMEbus version for machines like the SunSPARCstation.andP;  The link will transfer data and images between NuBus andVME-bus machines but doesn't provide for translation.andM;The AL 101 NuBus link and the AL 102 VME link cost $3,699 each.andP;  Fiber-opticcabling usually sells for less than $1 per foot, but the card also can beconfigured to work with less-expensive coaxial cable, he said.andM;Augment Systems Inc. is at 19 Crosby Drive, Bedford, Mass.andP;  01730-1419.andO;Phone (617) 271-0230; fax (617) 275-4461.andO;</TEXT></DOC>